Definition: a blood test to detect syphilis
Example: a complement fixation test is used to detect antibodies to the syphilis organism treponema; a positive reaction indicates the presence of antibodies and therefore syphilis infection
Synonyms: Wasserman_reaction, Wassermann, complement_fixation_test, a, blood, test, to, detect, syphilis, complement, fixation, is, used, antibodies, the, organism, treponema, positive, reaction, indicates, presence, of, and, therefore, infection
Category: noun.cognition
